cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks, specifically on attentional models for videos. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel model that learns from human fixation data, which involves machine learning techniques such as deep 3D convolutional features and long short-term memory networks. This suggests that the paper could also belong to categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with videos, which could place it in categories such as cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
